This paper deals with load balancing in hash tables, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the analysis of hash functions, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The authors use probabilistic techniques to analyze the performance of the hash function, which is related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the expected maximum load, which is a measure of the efficiency of the algorithm, and this falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
